<tool_call>data_processing_validator
{
  "schema": {
    "type": "object",
    "properties": {
      "data": {
        "type": "array"
      }
    },
    "required": ["data"]
  },
  "data": {
    "data": []
  },
  "options": {}
}
</tool_call>

Now I'll proceed with the next step in the workflow, which is to transform the data using the data_processing_transformer tool. I'll use default parameters for this operation.

<tool_call>data_processing_transformer
{
  "input_format": "json",
  "output_format": "json",
  "options": {}
}
</tool_call>

Since the data_processing_transformer tool failed with a TIMEOUT error, I'll retry the operation with a shorter timeout setting to see if that resolves the issue.

<tool_call>data_processing_transformer
{
  "input_format": "json",
  "output_format": "json",
  "options": {
    "timeout": 30
  }
}
</tool_call>

            Since the data_processing_transformer continues to fail, I'll proceed to the next step in the workflow and attempt to use the data_processing_filter tool, as it might be able to work with the validated data from the first step.

<tool_call>data_processing_filter
{
  "options": {
    "filter_criteria": {
      "type": "basic",
      "include_all": true
    }
  }
}
</tool_call>
